data.title: Monroe County, FL - Official Website
data.text:
The following bus routes service Monroe County. Bus Routes subject to change without notice. The Lower Keys Shuttle services from Key West to Marathon and Dade-Monroe bus services Florida City to Ocean Reef and to Marathon. Both offer several stops along US1.

Lower Keys Shuttle

The Lower Keys Shuttle is provided by the City of Key West and services stops along US1 from Key West to Marathon.

Miami-Dade to Monroe Bus (JGT)

Miami-Dade County provides Upper and Middle Keys Service to the Florida Keys along US1.

Dade-Monroe Bus (JGT)

ROUTE #301 (Florida City to Key Largo, Tavernier, Islamorada, and Marathon)

Express service seven days a week. Travels from the Park and Ride Lot at the 344 Street Transit Way station in Florida City to Key Largo at Mile Marker 98, Tavernier at Mile Marker 87, Islamorada at Mile Marker 74, and Marathon at Mile Marker 50 along US1.

Route #301 Direct Webpage

Route #301 Weekday Monroe County US1 Northbound Schedule

Route #301 Weekday Monroe County US1 Southbound Schedule

Route #302 (Card Sound to Ocean Reef)

Express service seven days a week, two trips in the morning and afternoon. Travels from Florida City City Hall to Ocean Reef Club (only employees are admitted beyond the entrance to the club) in North Key Largo along W. Palm Dr, US 1, and Card Sound Road.
